Business Week presents: The Fifth Annual Digital Economy Conference,
Getting Down to Business: The B2B Boom, December 5-6, 2000 at The
Fairmont Hotel in San Francisco, California.

For a complete listing of speakers, full program details or to register
go to: http://www.conferences.businessweek.com/2000/digital
or e-mail: digital_economy@businessweek.com

Event topics include Exchanges: What do they mean for collaboration,
prices and profitability; Mobile Net: How far, how fast?; Technology on
Tap: How will it transform your business?; Supply Chain Management: How
integrated must the digital corporation be?; Policy: Was the Microsoft
case just the beginning?

Special dinner entertainment by Jay Leno, Host of The Tonight Show


